# Assets Cash And Liquid Assets Negotiable Certificates Of Deposit Amount

## identifier
de7831

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, for negotiable certificates of deposit (NCD). NCDs are short-term debt securities, repayable at a fixed date. The NCD trades at a discount from face value.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.CashAndLiquidAssets.NCD.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo7.02.06
- period=instant
